properties.name: East Coast Site 1 (EC1 â€“ near CP B1)
properties.description:
There is a public carpark behind and to the west of this site (B1) and the carpark at Big Splash east of this site.
Plenty of debris inland and along the coast but beware of a large boat storage area where hazardous equipment lie around.
Participants should drop weighted rubbish off at lampposts, taking note of the lamppost numbers so as for us to arrange with NEA to pick up the trash and during bad weather, chill out in pavilion shelters to the west of the site.

properties.name: East Coast Site 2 (nr Big Splash)
properties.description:
Rather lengthy stretch with moderate trash load.
Participants may park in carpark at Big Splash and deposit weighted trash at lampposts, taking note of the lamppost numbers so as for us to arrange with NEA to pick up the trash.
Pavilion shelters are available for shelter from bad weather.
Participants to beware of sharp edges when collecting rubbish among rocks around Jetty

properties.name: East Coast Site 3 (around Parkland Green)
properties.description: Moderate trash load. Participants should drop trash off at lampposts, taking note of the lamppost numbers so as for us to arrange with NEA to pick up the trash. Pavilions available for shelter and participants to park at public carpark

properties.name: East Coast Site 4
properties.description: Moderate to heavy trash load, especially inland areas. Weighted trash may be deposited at at lampposts, taking note of the lamppost numbers so as for us to arrange with NEA to pick up the trash. Pavilions are available for participants to take shelter and ample parking space available at public carpark beside Marina Cove

properties.name: East Coast Site 6
properties.description: Participants to drop trash off at lampposts, taking note of the lamppost numbers so as for us to arrange with NEA to pick up the trash

properties.name: East Coast Site 8
properties.description: To beware and keep away from boat storage area for safety of participants

properties.name: Tanah Merah Site 2
properties.description:
Light Trash load, do pay particular attention to fishing lines inland.
Weighted trash needs to be dropped off at lampposts, taking note of the lamppost numbers so as for us to arrange with NEA to pick up the trash.
Parking is available at public carpark before entrance to National Sailing Centre
In case of bad weather, there is no suitable shelter and participants should turn to shelter in National Sailing Centre where toilets can also be found.

properties.name: Tanah Merah Site 3

Large group to look after Sites 3 to 5

properties.name: Tanah Merah Site 6
properties.description:
May have no trespassing state land signs here; to check during recce before picking site.

Advisable group around 150 adultsHeavy recreational trash load but weighted trash needs to be dropped off at lampposts, taking note of the lamppost numbers so as for us to arrange with NEA to pick up the trash. No children advised due to unsuitable terrain. For shelter from bad weather, and toilets look to MOE CCAC or neighboring NSRCC Sea Sports Centre. Parking may be found at NSRCC Sea Sports Centre

properties.name: Tanah Merah Site 7
properties.description:
NO TRESPASSING FROM OCT 2013.
Special permission for access from SPF via SLA.
Trash to be dropped off at the seawall near the far corner (closest the beach) of the Tanah Merah Ferry Terminal car park fence.
Request permission from Singapore Cruise Centre for volunteers access through the car park gate.

OIC to proceed to the Pass Office located at the ground level to collect the keys for the back gate from the duty manager.

properties.name: Sungei Pandan mangrove (SP1), new site for 2015
properties.description: Sungei Pandan Mangrove site SP1 along the western bank of the river. The site requires sensitive removal of trash, as the soft substrate is easily impacted. Requires additional recce. The adjacent Pandan Reservoir Service Road is accessible by a lorry for trash removal.

properties.name: Sungei Pandan Mangrove (SP3), proposed new site for recce
properties.description: Eastern bank of Sungei Pandan, has not been recce-d yet.

properties.name: Sungei Pandan Mangrove (SP2)
properties.description: Sungei Pandan Mangrove site SP2 along the western bank of the river is a small site with a high amount of accumulated trash. It is largely a soft and muddy terrain with no shelter or public toilet. The Meeting and Trash Collection Points are situated at an adjacent bus stop (no. 25) along Jalan Buroh.

properties.name: West  Coast Park
properties.description: Consists of 2 small stretches of sandy beach with many small boats parked. Patches of mangrove. Public toilets and shelters are available. Trash load moderately high. About 40-50pax sufficient.

properties.name: Labrador Rocky Shore
properties.description: Site closed by order of BCA due to safety concerns on slope stability.

properties.name: Berlayar Creek
properties.description: Berlayar Creek is a small stretch of mangrove that is currently accessible from the mouth of the creek. Not easy for participants not familiar walking in mud. Load is not high but widely dispersed. Meeting point is carpark C of Labrador park. Toilets and shelters are nearby. 20 pax sufficient.

properties.name: Marina East Beach
properties.description: This beach site is out of bounds to public and will be accessed by Waterways Watch Society.

properties.name: Chek Jawa North 1 & North 2
properties.description: Required a very early start to cross at a suitable low tide.

properties.name: Mamam Beach (Closed)
properties.description:
Man-made rocky shore; trash caught between rocks. Difficult to get around.
Not suitable for families and children; best for "garang" adults.
Pointless at higher tides - no beach.

properties.name: Nordin Beach (Closed)
properties.description:
Beach (sandy) is severely eroded.
Relatively low trash load.
Has toilet and shelter at the beach.
About 200m plus?

properties.name: Ketam Beach 3
properties.description:
The fourth and fifth left turns from the main paths lead to Ketam Beaches 2 and 3.

The beach is mainly gravelly, with lots of small bits of trash. Each section is about 150m plus.

properties.name: Ketam Beach 2
properties.description:
The fourth and fifth left turns from the main paths lead to Ketam Beaches 2 and 3.

The beach is mainly gravelly, with lots of small bits of trash. Each section is about 150m plus.

properties.name: Ketam Beach 1
properties.description:
Need to go along the bike path past the German Girl's Shrine (will see its yellow roof from main path), then walk through a single line of trees to get to this stretch of gravel beach.
It's just a 50-60m stretch of beach, demarcated on the left by trees and on the right by a bunch of foundation poles for an old jetty.
Terrain is fairly family friendly. No major shelter nor toilets nearby.
